      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "…not as good as one would hope.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Pessimists often get it wrong by underestimating how quickly people adapt.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "And optimists? ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "They",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": " get it wrong by ignoring that facets of things that could potentially lead to ruin.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "It often doesn’t pay to be pessimist. Nor does it help to be a tried and true optimist.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "What helps is having the audacity to believe that a better version of the future you predict will exist. While hedging your bets for inevitable hardships and staying cognizant of your blindspots.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Better’s possible. But not without error.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}